<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-01-19T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-19T19:00:00-05:00" n="513" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d513">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">394.31/1—1951: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Acting Chairman of the United States Delegation to the Torquay
                                Conference</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Corse</hi></persName>)<note n="1" xml:id="d513fn1">Repeated to
                                Paris for <gloss target="#t_OSR1">OSR</gloss> as 3831.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left">
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                                <lb/>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                            </seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-01-19T19:00:00-05:00">January
                                    19, 1951—7 p. m</date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>325. From State, <gloss target="#t_Treas1">Treas</gloss>, Gomineree,
                            Labor, EGA and <gloss target="#t_Agric1">Agric</gloss>. Re <gloss target="#t_Deptel1">Deptel</gloss> 316, Jan 15 and <gloss target="#t_Deltel1">Deltel</gloss>s 354 and 355, Jan 17.</p>
                        <p>1. Regret instrs refDeptel did not sufficiently emphasize view here US
                            shld lend strong active support to Blankenstein proposal, rather than
                            qualified concurrence reported <gloss target="#t_Deltel1">Deltel</gloss>
                            355.</p>
                        <p>2. We are still of view every reasonable measure shld be taken make
                            tangible progress on Blakenstein proposal before Torquay adjournment. We
                            are concerned failure obtain results will lead to: (<hi rend="italic">a</hi>) new proposals for preferential low-tariff club in <gloss target="#t_Eur1">Eur</gloss>; (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) stalemate
                            in trade liberalization program; (<hi rend="italic">c</hi>) <gloss target="#t_Benelux1">Benelux</gloss> disaffection of Torquay negots
                            and <gloss target="#t_GATT1">GATT</gloss> in gen.</p>
                        <pb facs="1344" n="1328" xml:id="pg_1328"/>
                        <p>3. If extension longer than one week wld increase possibility positive
                            results on Blankenstein proposal, we request <gloss target="#t_TAC1">TAC</gloss> reconsider position reported <gloss target="#t_Deltel1">Deltel</gloss> 355 para 4a in order recommend and support to <gloss target="#t_CP1">CP</gloss>’s longer extension.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>